==German==
===Etymology===
Compare Old-English ''[[freo]]'', from Proto-Germanic *''[[frijaz]]'', which derives from Proto Indo-European *''[[prijos-]]'', dear, beloved; compare English ''[[free]]'' and Dutch ''[[vrij]]''

===Pronunciation===
/[[Pronunciation guide|frai]]/
===Adjective and Adverb===
# Not [[imprisoned]] or [[enslaved]]: ''ein freier [[Mann]]''
# Not [[blocked]]: ''Der Weg ist frei.''
# (''as a suffix'') Without. ''[[Blei]]frei; frei von Schadstoffen''
# Un[[limit]]ed (rarely). ''Ihm wurde freie [[Hand]] für alle Maßnahmen gegeben.''
# For which no [[payment]] is necessary (''nowadays mostly in set idioms''): ''freier Eintritt'', ''Freibier''

